#--script smb-vuln-*
It run this script’s :
• smb-vuln-conficker.nse – Checks for systems vulnerable to the Conficker worm via SMB.
• smb-vuln-cve2009-3103.nse – Detects SMB vulnerability related to CVE-2009-3103 causing remote crash or code execution.
• smb-vuln-cve-2017-7494.nse – Tests for Samba remote code execution vulnerability (CVE-2017-7494).
• smb-vuln-ms06-025.nse – Checks for MS06-025 SMB vulnerability allowing remote code execution.
• smb-vuln-ms07-029.nse – Detects MS07-029 vulnerability in SMB services.
• smb-vuln-ms08-067.nse – Checks for MS08-067, a critical SMB remote code execution flaw.
• smb-vuln-ms10-054.nse – Tests for MS10-054 SMB client vulnerability.
• smb-vuln-ms10-061.nse – Detects MS10-061 SMB Print Spooler remote code execution vulnerability.
• smb-vuln-ms17-010.nse – Checks for MS17-010 (EternalBlue) SMB vulnerability.
• smb-vuln-regsvc-dos.nse – Tests for SMB registry service denial-of-service vulnerability.
• smb-vuln-webexec.nse – Checks for SMB web execution vulnerability allowing remote command execution.



